personalInfo.education: Auburn University (2013, Interdisciplinary Studies, Business and Psychology)

tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished 4th at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Played in 10 Web.com Tour events, making six cuts. Had two top-25s, a T13 at the News Sentinel Open, where he closed with a 63...Added a T16 at the Nova Scotia Open...Finished 117th on the Regular Season money list and 137th on the final year-long money list.

2014: Played in five Web.com Tour events, making two cuts, both T9s. Finished 117th on the final money list. First T9 came when he carded 67-69-70 over 54 holes of BMW Charity Pro-Am. Made back-to-back eagles in the final round, including a hole-in-one on No.15, for a 65...Second top-10 came three months later, at the Price Cutter Charity Championship. Opened 68-68 then moved into contention with a 7-under 65 in the third round at Highland Springs CC. Shot a 3-under 69 on the final day to T9 with Nick Taylor, three shots behind winner Cameron Percy...Was 2014 NGA Player of the Year and Rookie of the Year, winning four times...Finished T64 at Q-School Finals.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was a two-time All-American (2012 and 2013) at Auburn University, where he earned three collegiate victories. Finished runner-up in the individual portion of the 2013 NCAA Championship.
tourBios.personal: Favorite golf memory was beating his dad for the first time...First-tee intro song would be "Shoulder Lean" by Young Dro...Favorite professional teams are the New York teams, the Yankees, Jets, Knicks and Rangers...Favorite courses are Pumpkin Ridge, East Lake and Oak Hill and athletes are LeBron James, Kobe Bryant, Bo Jackson and Deion Sanders...Biggest thrill outside golf was graduating from college...Would like to be featured in Sports Illustrated one day...Best sporting event ever attended was the 2013 Iron Bowl (Auburn vs. Alabama) where Auburn's Chris Davis returned a missed field goal opportunity for a touchdown to win the game and earn a trip to the SEC Championship...Twitter handle is @dombozzelli.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T9th at the Panama Claro Championship.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T24th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Web.com Tour.
